    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But when ye shall hear of wars and commotions,.... Or seditions and tumults; \"wars\" may design the wars of the Romans, against the Jews; and the \"commotions\", or seditions, the internal troubles among themselves: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "be not terrified; as if the destruction of the nation, city, and temple, would be at once: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for these things must first come to pass, but the end is not by and by; or \"immediately\". The Syriac, Arabic, and Persic versions leave out this last word, and read, as in See Gill on Matthew 24:6. ",
